summary:
Economist research consultant with intrinsic motivation for Data Science & Data Analysis. With international experience in the United Nations and medium-large financial corporations. 
Raised on an entrepreneur-culture network in the north-east part of Santiago (Chile). Out-of-the-box data-driven thinker with innovation as a purpose. 

With applied knowledge on Machine Learning, and Unsupervised Learning. As thesis topic studied the impact of Central Bank speeches in the overnight rate through a sentiment analysis and topic modeling.

Personality: üåéüåçüåè
Open-minded, social, adaptable, creative, flexible, and multidisciplinary.

üìëAcademic Background:
- MSc Economics specialization in Data Science
- Business Engineering BSc in Economics from the University of Chile.
- Bachelor in Social Sciences and Humanities.

 üå±
Spanish - German - English - Dutch

üíªüí°Tools: 
- Python
- R
- Stata
- Excel - Macros
- Latex
- Octave
- Redatam 7
